OL,3,CSix police officers to face misconduct
OL,4,Chearings over crash that left three
OL,5,Cdead
OL,7,FConcerns included communication with
OL,8,Frelatives, how information provided by
OL,9,Ffamilies was followed up, and how the
OL,10,Ftwo forces worked together. The IOPC
OL,11,Ffound that in more than half of the
OL,12,Fcases, the service provided was
OL,13,Funacceptable.
OL,15,FSeveral officers and staff will take
OL,16,Fpart in a reflective practice review
OL,17,Fprocess to address the issues raised.
OL,19,FFollowing the inquiry, the IOPC
OL,20,Fdetermined that six officers should
OL,21,Fface disciplinary proceedings.
