OL,7,FThe IOPC also reviewed more than 30
OL,8,Fcomplaints made by the families of
OL,9,Fthose involved about how both Gwent
OL,10,FPolice and South Wales Police handled
OL,11,Fthe investigation. Concerns included
OL,12,Fcommunication with relatives, how
OL,13,Finformation provided by families was
OL,14,Ffollowed up, and how the two forces
OL,15,Fworked together. The IOPC found that
OL,16,Fin more than half of the cases, the
OL,17,Fservice provided was unacceptable.
OL,18,FSeveral officers and staff will take
OL,19,Fpart in a reflective practice review
OL,20,Fprocess to address the issues raised.
